programmes.show_name: Shoplifters & Scammers: At War with the Law
programmes.show_description: It's nightfall in London's West End, and undercover detectives Steve and Adam are on patrol when they get a call from a famous department store on Oxford Street.
Alex pulls over a young drunk driver trying to impress his mates. A self-declared successful businesswoman is over twice the legal limit.
Drink drivers are increasingly trying to come up with ways to beat the system. One driver claims to have had a single swig of beer, forcing the cops to wait 20 minutes.
Derbyshire's road crime team launch a crackdown on drugs supply lines, using intelligence and surveillance tactics. Operation Spacedust targets county line networks.
Officers chase car thieves through the Essex suburbs, break up a nightclub fight and tackle some boy racers in sunny Southend.
The interceptors chase a stolen 4x4, give a couple of car thieves an early wake-up call and tackle a road-tax evader.
Stanway Police are first on the scene of a bad car crash on a country road. Four cop cars pursue a speeding jeep down the M25.
A holidaymaker sees his claim crash and burn and in the USA, justice is delivered for the woman whose sickening health insurance fraud saw an innocent man jailed.
Off The Rails kicks off. Mali's got big plans. Will Leah derail the platform party?
Eddie pops the question. Has Leah gone too far? Abigail's in hot water.
It's a busy night at Barnsley Hopsital's casualty department, so when Sister Benita arrives to head the shift, the corridors are already packed full of patients.
Benjamin arrives with a sore throat, worried a rugby tackle has caused internal bleeding. Kate's family history of blood clots raises concern, leading Dr Anna to arrange an ultrasound.
A patient is flown in by air ambulance after falling down a ditch with her mobility scooter; a woman is treated after impaling her eye on a tent peg and an ankle needs treatment.
There's major trauma when a hay bale lands on a farmer's head in a remote location. Plus a battle to save a man in cardiac arrest, and a 76-year-old woman has fallen down the stairs.
Dr Dev Shah faces an eyeball-sized cyst on a patient's cheek, while Dr Toby Nelson tries to evict a troublesome lipoma called Janet.

programmes.show_name: Call the Bailiffs: Time to Pay Up!
programmes.show_description: Enforcement Agent Alex aims to collect a huge £35k debt, while Mark and Sam trail a woman who owes more than a year's worth of rent - a sizable £25k - to a previous landlord.
Documentary series. A tanning salon owner offers to rent his home to an employee, who upsets the neighbours with her parties and owes him 3,000 in back rent.
Phillip is dizzy and disorientated, and his GP suspects an amnesiac disorder. Already on anti-anxiety meds, Karen may have PTSD, so is referred for psychiatric assessment.
Dr Toby Nelson faces the prospect of removing a lipoma that's underneath a patient's tattoo. Dr Natalia Spierings aims to make a groom-to-be picture perfect for his wedding photos.
Challengers 'The Crabapples', a family team from St Albans, try to defeat the Eggheads to win the rolling prize fund. (Ep5)

programmes.show_description: At 8.40pm on a quiet night in a local convenience store in Derbyshire, two masked men storm into the store and knock the shop assistant to the ground.
Derbyshire's finest face a series of issues with motorcyclists - with one evading them for over an hour in a high-speed chase.
A look at officers from Derbyshire's road teams facing the daily challenges of policing our streets whilst single crewed.
Action-packed observational documentary series with Jamie Theakston. Alex and Jason chase down a gang of teenage suspects on foot through a housing estate.
The interceptors have to drop everything when a speeding 4x4 rushes past them. The Stanway team pursues a man with a machete.
A look back at the highlights of the series, including efforts to catch a stolen 4x4 that tries to run a police Evo off the road.
The team joins forces with the chopper to track down a wanted criminal on a motorbike, and a young driver crashes straight into an unmarked police car.
The Police close in on a cash for crash gang, the diagnosis isn't good for a traveller's bogus medical claim and a tailor's claim for expensive suits ruined by sewage goes down the pan.
Eddie pops the question. Has Leah gone too far? Abigail's in hot water.
David leads a rescue operation. Tane and Levi risk their lives for love. Who will make it out of the trainwreck alive?
Dr Amir Khan removes the biggest lipoma he has ever seen from Nigel's chest. Vanda was told she had only two years to live, but Dr Chris Harris offers a more positive prognosis.
A two-year-old girl is brought in as she deals with dangerously low blood sugar levels; junior doctor Alex Chatburn has his own views on emergency admissions.
Cara has fallen 50 metres down a waterfall. She has multiple obvious injuries that need urgent care, but Dr Richard Fawcett must also investigate hidden internal injuries.
A driver who has crashed into another car passes a breath test but his behaviour is a cause for concern. And in Kent, a lorry crashes into a railway bridge and the driver runs off.
